wiki.content: "What Do You Mean?" is a song by Canadian singer Justin Bieber and the lead single for his fourth album Purpose (2015). It is Bieber's first No. 1 single on the Billboard Hot 100. It makes him the youngest male to debut at No. 1 on the Billboard Hot 100, earning him a Guinness Record. It is only the 23rd song in the Hot 100's 57-year history to debut at No. 1. Justin Bieber co-wrote "What Do You Mean?" with Jason Boyd and Mason Levy. The song was produced by Bieber, and MdL who had previously collaborated with the singer on his single "Boyfriend" (2012). It is a pop song, with tropical house influences. "What Do You Mean?" was heavily promoted by artists, actors and talk show hosts upon it's release, with Ruby Rose, James Corden, Mariah Carey, J Balvin, Lil Dicky, Kylie Jenner, Shaq, Travi$ Scott, Ashley Benson, Ariana Grande, The Fat Jew, Halsey, Big Sean, Little Mix, Ed Sheeran, Madison Beer, Fifth Harmony, Meghan Trainor, Luke Bryan, CL, Alanis Morissette, Christina Perri, Tony Hawk, Austin Mahone, Rudy Mancuso, Hilary Duff, Twenty One Pilots, F*ck Jerry, Tori Kelly, Ryan Sheckler, Hailee Steinfeld, Usher, Matt Lauer and Savannah Guthrie, John Leguizamo, Jack & Jack, Martin Garrix, Will Ferrell, Ashton Kutcher, Dan + Shay, Ellen Degeneres, Doug the Pug, Xenia Deli, Gigi Hadid, Carly Rae Jepsen, Chris Marten, King Bach and Anwar Jibawi, G-Dragon, Elvis Duran, Tyler Oakley, Ben Stiller, Kendall Jenner, Little Big Town, Larry King, Jason Derulo, Kate Hudson, Cody Simpson, SÃ©bastien Cauet, Mark Wahlberg, Chris Paul, Michael Buble, Maejor, Florida Georgia Line, Jiff the Pomeranian, Jaden Smith, Steven Tyler, Todrick Hall, Kevin Hart, Miley Cyrus, Rory Kramer, Marnie the Dog, Alec Baldwin, Skrillex, Jaxon Bieber, Martha Stewart, Britney Spears, Florido Basallo.
